for input from user : package bufio

If you write backends and Apis, a lot of parameters come to you via a string or URl,
This urls , when you convert them can give you potential causes/crashes.


------------------------------

b := a          (b gets assigns a copy of a in primitive, structs, arrays) // unless a pointer is used
        change b wont change a

                (b references to a in slices, maps)
        change b changes a

------------------------------

1. create a folder
2. make a main.go
3. $ go mod init <folder name>
3. $ go mod init <folder/module name>          // to make a module to export

-----------------------------

time is strict

-----------------------------

in the environment, we have different variables

$ go env

One of them is GOOS ( or goos )

$ GOOS="windows" go build       : to  build windows executable , automatically finds the main.go file

$ GOOS="darwin" go build        : to build mac executable

$ GOOS="linux" go build         : to build linux executable

-----------------------------

Memory management:  Memory alloc and dealloc happens automatically
                    garb collec. is automatic
                    out of scope becomes nil

new() and make()

new()   : alloc memory but not initialized
        : zeroed storage

make()  : alloc mem and initializes
        : non-zeroed storage

